  <p id="1">
    <s id="1:1">The Noble</s>
  </p>
  <p id="2">
    <s id="2:1">Dhāraṇī of Tārā</s>
  </p>
  <p id="3">
    <s id="3:1">The Translation</s>
  </p>
  <p id="4">
    <s id="4:1"><milestone xml:id="UT22084-094-006-19"/>Homage to the Three Jewels!</s>
  </p>
  <p id="5">
    <s id="5:1"><milestone xml:id="UT22084-094-006-22"/>namo ratna­trayāya | nama āryāvalokiteśvarāya bodhisattvāya mahā­sattvāya mahā­kāruṇikāya |<note xml:id="UT22084-094-006-23"/></s>
  </p>
  <p id="6">
    <s id="6:1"><milestone xml:id="UT22084-094-006-24"/>tad yathā | oṁ tāre tuttāre<note xml:id="UT22084-094-006-25"/> ture sarva­duṣṭa­praduṣṭān mama kṛte jambhaya stambhaya mohaya bandhaya hūṁ hūṁ hūṁ phaṭ phaṭ phaṭ sarva­duṣṭa­stambhani tāre svāhā |<note xml:id="UT22084-094-006-26"/></s>
  </p>
  <p id="7">
    <s id="7:1"><milestone xml:id="UT22084-094-006-27"/>This concludes “The Noble Dhāraṇī of Tārā.”</s>
  </p>
</text>
